==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Resinous
<hw>Res"in*ous</hw> <pr>(-?s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>resinous</ets>: cf. F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧sineux</ets>. See
<er>Resin</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to resin; of the nature of
resin; resembling or obtained from resin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Resinous electricity</b></col> <fld>(Elec.)</fld>,
<cd>electricity which is exited by rubbing bodies of the resinous kind.
See <cref>Negative electricity</cref>, under
<er>Negative</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resinously</ent>⟦br⟧
